# ðŸŒŽ Earthquake Visualizer


## Overview
A clean, responsive React app built with **Tailwind CSS** and **React-Leaflet** to visualize recent earthquakes around the world using the **USGS Earthquake API**.


### Features
- Interactive map (Leaflet) with zoom & popups
- Circle markers sized by magnitude and colored by depth
- Slider to filter earthquakes by minimum magnitude
- Responsive UI (works on both mobile and desktop)
- Graceful error handling and loading states


## API Used
**USGS Earthquake API:**
```
https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/feed/v1.0/summary/all_day.geojson
```


## How to Deploy


### ðŸ”¹ 1. CodeSandbox / StackBlitz
1. Go to [https://codesandbox.io/](https://codesandbox.io/) or [https://stackblitz.com/](https://stackblitz.com/)
2. Create a new **Vite + React** sandbox.
3. Add dependencies: `react-leaflet`, `leaflet`, `tailwindcss`.
4. Copy all files from this project.
5. Click **Share â†’ Live** to get your deployed URL.


### ðŸ”¹ 2. Netlify
1. Push your project to GitHub.
2. Go to [https://app.netlify.com/](https://app.netlify.com/).
3. Click **Add new site â†’ Import from GitHub**.
4. Choose your repo â†’ Build command: `npm run build`, Publish directory: `dist`.
5. Click **Deploy Site**.


### ðŸ”¹ 3. Vercel
1. Install Vercel CLI or use the web dashboard.
2. Run `vercel` in your project directory.
3. It automatically detects Vite â†’ deploys your site with a unique URL.


